The events for Neighborhood Warming Initiatives 2020 Photo: Courtesy of Yu Fei A series of exhibitions, tours and workshops have been included in the Neighborhood Warming Initiatives 2020, which aims to explore the bond between the White Pagota, a landmark building in the urban area of Beijing, and its surrounding neighborhood. As part of the ongoing Beijing Design Week, the initiatives hope to involve the neighborhood and warm the ancient city area with arts and design events. These exhibitions include showcase photos that record the changes, innovation and improved living environment in the area as well as the community bonds that formed during the fight against COVID-19 in early 2020. Additionally, mini-fairs, an opera arts showcase and forum will be hosted during the event, which ends on Thursday.  
